# OpenObject License

OpenObject is proprietary software. Its source is published publicly for
transparency and so that people can run it: first, to turn an ordinary computer
and monitor into a full-screen art display, and also to revive and operate an
Infinite Objects XXL frame. Publishing the source does not place it in the public
domain or grant any license to use it, except the limited permission stated
below. All other rights are reserved by Queueue Studios LLC.

## What you may do

You may download, install, run, and update OpenObject to operate your own display
or frame for personal, noncommercial use. This includes the copies needed to do
so, such as cloning this repository onto a device you own and updating it in
place.

